summary: God, imagine in Avengers 4... What would life be like once Tony’s back on earth? He reunites with the remaining Avengers and...
body:
God, imagine in Avengers 4…

What would life be like once Tony’s back on earth? He reunites with the remaining Avengers and they all quickly realize that they need to figure out a way to undo what Thanos has done. 

Tony, who’s been uncharacteristically quiet ever since the battle on Titan, is ready to sit back and let the others handle it. After all, he spent six years preparing for Thanos but they all still lost. He thinks, what good is he to the team anyway? He should have died on Titan. He shouldn’t be here. So he’s going to make himself scarce. Tony doesn’t want to bring more harm to the team just because he was trying to do good. The last few times he did, Ultron happened, then the team split up, and now half the universe is gone.

But the team is quick to convince him how important he is. Especially Steve, who tells Tony, over and over, that he’s earth’s best defender. Without Tony, there is no team.

Slowly but surely, Tony regains some of his confidence. He doesn’t do well with being idle anyway, so he and the Avengers sit down and work out a game plan. And they all agree that in order to succeed, they need as many brains working together as possible, to come up with new ideas, new solutions, new defense strategies, new tech.

Steve and Bruce get Shuri on board and she flies to New York to work with the team while Okoye and M’Baku look after Wakanda. And Tony calls up this other kid he’d been mentoring on the down low for the last six years. Harley Keener comes to the compound, ready to get down to business and help Iron Man just like he did back in Tennessee all those years ago.

Tony sets Shuri and Harley up in the biggest lab available in the compound. He watches as the two of them quickly get to know each other and become friends. They work so well together, just like Tony and Bruce.

But everywhere he looks, Tony can’t help but feel this incredible, gaping hole that only one person can fill. He sees Shuri and Harley messing around in the lab and he knows the picture isn’t complete.

Peter should be here, he thinks. Peter would have loved meeting Shuri and Harley, talking science and technology with them. And Shuri and Harley both deserve someone as wonderful as Peter in their lives.

The world can only improve if the next generation of great minds is there to guide it. And right now? It’s missing one of its brightest.

And it’s with this thought in mind that Tony strengthens his resolve to do everything he can to make things right.

summary: Fun fact...
body:
Fun fact…

Marvel’s first draft of Spider Man was called Doctor Arachnid and had powers that included trapping criminals in webs, paralysing with a sting, and draining life energy from enemies. This version was deemed to be too gory for Peter Parker’s storyline and was cut.
